<p>Every now and then I find myself tweaking the look of emacs and have started to build up a list of my own common faces in <code>custom-set-faces</code> to suit my needs, for example here is my current setup:</p>
<figure class="emacs-img"><img src="https://emacs.dyerdwelling.family/ox-hugo/20230819202723-emacs--Describe-Character-Under-Cursor.jpg">
</figure>

